All patients completed the study without data leakage. The average score of sleep quality before intervention in the two groups was not statistically significant (P = 0.927), and there was statistical significance after intervention (P < 0.05). The t-test results also showed that the average score of anxiety before intervention was not statistically significant (P = 0.713), and the average score of anxiety after intervention was statistically significant (P < 0.05) (Fig. 1, Fig. 2
) (Table 2
). In this study, compared with the control group, the experimental group had reduced anxiety levels and improved sleep quality after 5 days (Fig. 1, Fig. 2).
